  \begin {tikzcd}
    C\ar [rr, bend left, "F"] & \bot  & D\ar [ll, bend left, "G"]\makebox [0pt][l]\,
  \end {tikzcd}



 be an adjunction with unit
1_C\xrightarrow {\eta } GF and counit FG\xrightarrow {\epsilon } 1_D. Then: 
F is faithful if and only if each component of \eta  is monic;

F is full if and only if each component of \eta  is a retraction;

F is full and faithful if and only if \eta  is an isomorphism.

Dually: 
G is faithful if and only if  each component of \epsilon  is epic;

G is full if and only if each component of \epsilon  is a section;

G is full and faithful if and only if \epsilon  is an isomorphism.

Pullbacks preserve monomorphisms.
